  "prompt": "Would ambassador\u2019s child who studied in best universities make a good diplomat even though his/her native language skills are limited?",
  "response": "While having a prestigious educational background can be beneficial, language skills are crucial for diplomacy. A good diplomat typically needs:\n\n1. Strong language proficiency\n- Native or near-native fluency\n- Cultural understanding\n- Ability to communicate nuanced messages\n\n2. Educational advantages\n- Elite university education provides:\n- Critical thinking skills\n- International perspective\n- Networking opportunities\n\n3. Potential challenges\n- Limited language skills can:\n- Hinder effective communication\n- Create misunderstandings\n- Reduce credibility\n\n4. Recommended approach\n- Intensive language training\n- Long-term immersion\n- Cultural sensitivity training\n\n5. Relative importance\n- Language skills often matter more than background\n- Diplomatic effectiveness depends on communication abilities\n\nThe individual might need significant additional language and cultural preparation to be truly effective as a diplomat.",
